-# Bulk-action bar. It sits in the index toolbar (next to the search box), but its
-# buttons submit the BulkForm that wraps the table — `form: "BulkForm"` ties them
-# to that form so the checked `ids[]` ride along. Hidden until JS (cafe_car.js)
-# reveals it once at least one row is selected. The buttons loop the model policy's
-# `permitted_bulk_actions` (the source of truth); override this partial for a
-# bespoke set. Each button's label + style come from the locale (see #bulk_action).
.BulkActions{hidden: true, data: { bulk_bar: true }}
  - bulk_actions.each do |name|
    = bulk_action name
